Introduction

Woosung, also known as Sammy, is a South Korean-American singer-songwriter, producer, and musician. He is the leader, main vocalist, and guitarist of the boy band The Rose. In addition to his work with the group, he launched his solo career on July 25, 2019, with the release of his first mini-album, Wolf, under his independent label, Woolfpack.

Before pursuing music, Woosung played American football throughout junior high and high school in the United States until a shoulder injury led him to focus on music instead. Known for his love of animals, he even created an Instagram account for his Pomsky, Woolfy. In 2022, he joined Epik High as a special guest during their Epik High Is Here North America Tour.
